{"atom_id": "md_model04_a004", "file": "knowledge_base/model/04_associated_persons.md", "line_start": 7, "line_end": 7, "parent_section": "§4 [SDTM v2.0 — Chapter 4: Associated Persons Data]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Associated persons are individuals other than study subjects who can be associated with a study, a particular study subject, or a device used in the study.", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T12:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_model04_a005", "file": "knowledge_base/model/04_associated_persons.md", "line_start": 7, "line_end": 7, "parent_section": "§4 [SDTM v2.0 — Chapter 4: Associated Persons Data]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The structures of SDTM datasets that represent data about associated persons are based on the structures for data about study subjects, either general observation class structures or special-purpose domain structures.", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T12:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_model04_a006", "file": "knowledge_base/model/04_associated_persons.md", "line_start": 7, "line_end": 7, "parent_section": "§4 [SDTM v2.0 — Chapter 4: Associated Persons Data]", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "AP domains are created using SDTM variables, with the application of specific AP rules:", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T12:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_model04_a007", "file": "knowledge_base/model/04_associated_persons.md", "line_start": 9, "line_end": 9, "parent_section": "§4 [SDTM v2.0 — Chapter 4: Associated Persons Data]", "atom_type": "HEADING", "heading_level": 3, "sibling_index": 1, "verbatim": "### AP Domain Rules", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T12:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_model04_a008", "file": "knowledge_base/model/04_associated_persons.md", "line_start": 11, "line_end": 11, "parent_section": "§4 [SDTM v2.0 — Chapter 4: Associated Persons Data]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "1. **Prefix convention:** AP domains use the domain code prefix `AP` followed by the relevant domain code. For example, associated persons demographics would use `APDM`.", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T12:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_model04_a009", "file": "knowledge_base/model/04_associated_persons.md", "line_start": 13, "line_end": 13, "parent_section": "§4 [SDTM v2.0 — Chapter 4: Associated Persons Data]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "2. **APID:** The variable APID is used as an identifier in AP domains (instead of USUBJID for subjects). APID was removed from Section 3.1.4 (Identifiers for All Classes) because APID is only allowed in AP domains. It is still listed in Section 3 as an identifier.", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T12:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_model04_a010", "file": "knowledge_base/model/04_associated_persons.md", "line_start": 15, "line_end": 18, "parent_section": "§4 [SDTM v2.0 — Chapter 4: Associated Persons Data]", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "3. **Linking variables:**\n   - **RSUBJID** — Related Subject or Pool Identifier: identifies a related subject or pool of subjects. RSUBJID may be populated with the USUBJID of the related subject or the POOLID of the related pool. RSUBJID will be null for data about associated persons who are related to the study but not to any study subjects.\n   - **RDEVID** — Related Device Identifier: identifier for a related device. RDEVID will be populated with the SPDEVID of the related device.\n   - **SREL** — Subject, Device, or Study Relationship: if RSUBJID is populated, describes the relationship of the associated person(s) to the subject or pool identified in RSUBJID. If RDEVID is populated, describes the relationship to the device identified in RDEVID. If RSUBJID and RDEVID are null, SREL describes the relationship to the study identified in STUDYID.", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.8", "ts": "2026-04-29T12:00:00Z"}}
